Open or Create a Thematic Map
→ Load your map in QGIS.

Create a Print Layout
→ Project → New Print Layout
→ Enter a title → OK.

Add the Main Map
→ Add Item → Add Map
→ Draw the map area on the layout.
→ Go to Item Properties → Layers → Choose Map1.

Add a Picture (Logo/Inset)
→ Add Item → Add Picture
→ Place the picture box where needed.

Add Inset Overview
→ Select the main map picture from the Items pane.
→ Go to Item Properties → Overviews
→ Click + icon to add an overview.
→ Check Draw Overview
→ Choose the inset map (e.g., Map1) as the reference.
